{
  "brief": "# UX Research Brief: Bookmark List (Home Screen)\n\n**Project:** QuickMarks — Personal Bookmark Manager\n**Screen:** Bookmark List (`/`)\n**Brief Version:** 1.0\n**Prepared by:** UX Research Agent\n\n---\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\nThe Bookmark List is the primary screen of QuickMarks — the surface where users spend the vast majority of their time. It must simultaneously serve as a discovery tool, a filtering workspace, and a launch point for all CRUD actions. The design must balance a playful, warm visual personality with functional density, ensuring that retrieval feels instant, effortless, and even enjoyable for solo users managing a personal link collection.\n\n---\n\n## 2. User Needs Analysis\n\n### 2.1 Primary User Goals\n\n| Priority | Goal | Trigger Scenario |\n|----------|------|-----------------|\n| P0 | Find a bookmark quickly | \"I saved that CSS article last week — where is it?\" |\n| P0 | Understand what is saved at a glance | Opening the app after a few days away |\n| P1 | Filter by topic/category | \"Show me everything tagged `frontend`\" |\n| P1 | Add a new bookmark without friction | \"I want to save this link right now\" |\n| P2 | Edit or delete a stale bookmark | \"This URL is outdated, let me fix it\" |\n| P2 | Feel oriented even when the list is empty | First-time use or post-bulk-delete state |\n\n### 2.2 User Mental Models\n\n- Users expect this screen to behave like a **personal notebook index** — skimmable, personal, low-stakes.\n- Tag chips are conceptually similar to label filters in Gmail or Notion — users expect **multi-select with AND logic** to narrow results progressively.\n- The \"All\" chip maps to the familiar \"reset filters\" affordance; it must be visually distinct (always present, leftmost).\n- Relative timestamps (\"2h ago\") are preferred over absolute dates for recently saved items — they reinforce the \"living document\" feel.\n- Card hover revealing actions matches established patterns (Trello, Notion cards) — users on desktop expect icons to appear on hover; mobile users expect persistent visibility.\n\n### 2.3 Emotional Needs\n\nGiven the **playful, warm brand** (Fredoka headings, soft yellow cards, sticker energy), users should feel:\n- **Calm and in control** — not overwhelmed by a dense list\n- **Delighted by small details** — the FAB rotation, chip scale bounce, card shadow lift\n- **Reassured during destructive actions** — the inline flip confirmation (no modal) keeps context visible and feels lower-stakes\n\n---\n\n## 3. Information Architecture\n\n### 3.1 Content Hierarchy\n\n```\nBookmark List Screen\n├── Page Header / Brand Identity (implicit, via color + typography)\n├── Filter Zone (sticky / top)\n│   ├── SearchBar\n│   │   ├── Magnifying glass icon (leading)\n│   │   └── Text input (real-time, debounced ~150ms)\n│   └── TagFilterChips (horizontally scrollable row)\n│       ├── \"All\" chip (reset affordance, always first)\n│       └── [tag-1] [tag-2] … [tag-N] (derived from BookmarkStore.getAllTags())\n├── Content Zone (scrollable)\n│   ├── BookmarkCard (repeated, responsive grid)\n│   │   ├── Title (primary, truncated at 60 chars)\n│   │   ├── URL (secondary/muted, truncated)\n│   │   ├── Tag chips (max 3 visible + \"+N\" overflow)\n│   │   ├── Relative timestamp\n│   │   └── Actions (Edit | Delete)\n│   ├── EmptyState (zero bookmarks in store)\n│   └── NoResultsState (bookmarks exist but filters yield zero)\n└── FAB (fixed, bottom-right)\n```\n\n### 3.2 Filter Logic Architecture\n\n```\nBookmarkStore.getAll()\n        │\n        ▼\n [Step 1] Tag Filter\n  — If active tags exist: keep cards where card.tags includes ALL active tags (AND)\n  — If \"All\" selected or no active tags: pass through all\n        │\n        ▼\n [Step 2] Search Filter\n  — Case-insensitive substring match against card.title OR card.url\n  — Applied on top of tag-filtered results\n        │\n        ▼\n Rendered Card Grid\n```\n\n**Design implication:** Filter state (active tags + search query) should be visually summarised so users understand *why* they are seeing fewer results. The \"Clear filters\" affordance in `NoResultsState` must reset both dimensions simultaneously.\n\n### 3.3 State Matrix\n\n| BookmarkStore | Search Query | Tag Filter | Rendered State |\n|---------------|-------------|------------|----------------|\n| Empty | — | — | `EmptyState` |\n| Has items | Empty | None active | Full card grid |\n| Has items | Has value | None active | Filtered by search |\n| Has items | Empty | Tags active | Filtered by tags |\n| Has items | Has value | Tags active | Filtered by both |\n| Has items | Any | Any | Zero matches → `NoResultsState` |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Component Specifications\n\n### 4.1 SearchBar\n\n**Behaviour:**\n- Real-time filtering on every keystroke; debounce recommended at ~150ms to avoid jank on slow devices.\n- Clears via `×` icon button that appears only when input has value — keep the input clean when empty.\n- Placeholder text: `\"Search by title or URL…\"` (friendly, specific).\n- Input should be labelled with a visually hidden `<label>` or `aria-label=\"Search bookmarks\"` for screen readers.\n\n**Interaction notes:**\n- On mobile, tapping the bar should immediately focus and open the keyboard — no tap-to-reveal pattern.\n- The search does **not** filter tags — tag chips update independently.\n\n### 4.2 TagFilterChips\n\n**Behaviour:**\n- Source: `BookmarkStore.getAllTags()` — deduplicated, alphabetically sorted. \"All\" chip is prepended by the UI, not stored.\n- Multi-select AND logic: selecting `frontend` + `react` shows only cards tagged with *both*.\n- Selecting \"All\" deactivates all other chips and resets the tag filter.\n- If a chip is activated and then \"All\" is clicked, \"All\" becomes active and all others deactivate.\n- Chip row is **horizontally scrollable** on mobile; on desktop it may wrap or scroll depending on tag count.\n\n**Visual states:**\n| State | Style |\n|-------|-------|\n| Inactive | Outlined style — border in `--color-primary`, transparent fill, muted text |\n| Active | Filled style — `--color-primary` background, white/light text |\n| \"All\" active | Distinct filled style to signal \"no filter applied\" |\n| Hover | Scale 1.05, 100ms spring (per PRD micro-interaction spec) |\n\n**Accessibility:**\n- Chips implemented as `<button role=\"checkbox\" aria-checked=\"true/false\">` or a `<ul>` of toggle buttons.\n- \"All\" chip: `aria-label=\"Show all bookmarks, clear filters\"`.\n- Active state communicated via `aria-pressed` or `aria-checked`, not colour alone.\n\n### 4.3 BookmarkCard\n\n**Content display rules:**\n\n| Field | Display Rule |\n|-------|-------------|\n| `title` | Single line, `text-overflow: ellipsis`, max ~60 chars visible |\n| `url` | Single line, muted/secondary colour, truncated; not a clickable link on the card — opens via Detail or Edit |\n| `tags` | Max 3 chip badges shown; if more exist, show `+N` overflow indicator (e.g. `+2`) as a muted pill |\n| `createdAt` | Relative time string (e.g. \"2h ago\", \"3 days ago\") — recalculate on render, not stored as string |\n| Actions | Edit (pencil icon) + Delete (trash icon) |\n\n**Hover / focus behaviour:**\n- Shadow lifts from `0 2px 8px` → `0 6px 20px` (200ms ease).\n- On desktop: action icons (edit/delete) are **hidden by default**, revealed on hover/focus. Use `opacity: 0 → 1` transition, not `display: none`, so they remain in the focus order.\n- On mobile: action icons always visible (no hover state).\n\n**Delete inline confirmation flow:**\n1. User taps/clicks trash icon.\n2. Card **flips** (200ms crossfade) to show confirmation face: \"Delete this bookmark?\" + `[Confirm]` `[Cancel]` buttons.\n3. Focus is **trapped** within the confirmation face (per accessibility requirements).\n4. If no action taken within **5 seconds**, card auto-reverts to normal face.\n5. Confirm → calls `BookmarkStore.delete(id)`, card animates out of grid, no modal.\n6. Cancel → card flips back.\n\n**Keyboard navigation:**\n- `Tab` moves through cards in DOM order.\n- `Enter` on a card (not on an action button) navigates to the Detail screen or triggers Edit.\n- `Escape` while delete confirmation is open cancels and reverts.\n\n### 4.4 EmptyState\n\n**Trigger:** `BookmarkStore.getAll()` returns an empty array (no bookmarks exist yet).\n\n**Content:**\n- Illustration placeholder area (pulsing opacity animation: 2s infinite alternate, 0.6 → 1.0) — uses the brand's organic line-art / watercolor illustration style (botanicals, ribbon bookmarks, friendly doodles).\n- Heading: `\"No bookmarks yet\"` — Fredoka 24px.\n- Subtext: `\"Save your first link and it'll live right here.\"` — Inter 15px, muted.\n- CTA button: `\"Save your first link\"` → navigates to `/add`.\n\n**Design note:** This state should feel **inviting, not punishing** — the illustration and gentle pulse should communicate \"this is the beginning of something\", not an error.\n\n### 4.5 NoResultsState\n\n**Trigger:** Bookmarks exist in the store, but the current combination of tag filters + search query returns zero matches.\n\n**Content:**\n- No illustration needed — this is a transient, user-caused state.\n- Text: `\"No bookmarks match your filters\"` — Fredoka 20px.\n- Subtext clarifying what's active (optional enhancement): `\"Try a different search or clear your filters.\"` — Inter 15px, muted.\n- CTA: `\"Clear filters\"` text button — resets both search input and all active tag chips simultaneously.\n\n**Important distinction from EmptyState:** No CTA to add a bookmark. The user has bookmarks — they just can't see them. Directing them to add more would be confusing.\n\n### 4.6 FAB (Floating Action Button)\n\n**Placement:** Fixed, bottom-right. Minimum 24px from screen edges (safe area insets on mobile).\n**Icon:** `+` (Lucide or Phosphor filled/rounded style — never sharp outlined).\n**Colour:** `--color-primary` (`#6C5CE7`).\n**Micro-interaction:** 360° rotation on hover, 400ms ease-in-out.\n**Accessibility:**\n- `aria-label=\"Add new bookmark\"`.\n- Minimum touch target: 44×44px (per design token spec).\n- Must not obscure card actions when scrolled to bottom of list — consider scroll-aware hide/show on mobile if card density is high.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Interaction Patterns\n\n### 5.1 Filtering Interaction Flow\n\n```\nUser types in SearchBar\n        │\n        ▼ (debounced ~150ms)\nFilter state updates\n        │\n        ▼\nCard grid re-renders with matching subset\n        │\n   ┌────┴────┐\nZero results   Results exist\n   │               │\nNoResultsState   Updated grid\n```\n\n### 5.2 Tag Chip Toggle Flow\n\n```\nUser clicks inactive chip [tag-X]\n        │\n        ▼\nchip-X added to activeFilters[]\n        │\n        ▼\nGrid re-filters (tags AND logic + current search)\n        │\n        ▼\nChip animates: scale 1.0 → 1.05 → 1.0 (100ms spring)\nChip style: outlined → filled\n```\n\n### 5.3 Delete Confirmation Flow\n\n```\nUser clicks trash icon on card\n        │\n        ▼\nCard flips (200ms crossfade) → Confirmation face\n\"Delete this bookmark?\" [Confirm] [Cancel]\nFocus trapped inside confirmation face\n        │\n  ┌─────┴──────┐\n[Confirm]    [Cancel] or [Escape] or 5s timeout\n  │                │\nStore.delete()  Card flips back (200ms)\nCard exits grid\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Responsive Design Specifications\n\n### 6.1 Breakpoint Behaviour\n\n| Breakpoint | Grid Columns | Tag Row | Card Actions | FAB |\n|------------|-------------|---------|--------------|-----|\n| ≥ 1024px (Desktop) | 3 columns | Single row, may overflow scroll | Hidden, reveal on hover | Fixed BR, 24px margin |\n| 768–1023px (Tablet) | 2 columns | Horizontally scrollable | Hidden, reveal on hover | Fixed BR, 24px margin |\n| < 768px (Mobile) | 1 column | Horizontally scrollable | Always visible | Fixed BR, 16px margin |\n\n### 6.2 Responsive Card Anatomy\n\n- **Desktop:** Title + URL + tags + timestamp on one card face; generous padding (24px).\n- **Tablet:** Same structure, slightly reduced padding (20px).\n- **Mobile:** Full-width card; actions rendered as a persistent bottom strip on the card (not hidden). Tag chips on card truncate to max 2 + \"+N\" if needed to prevent wrapping.\n\n### 6.3 Touch Targets (Mobile)\n\nAll interactive elements must meet the **44×44px minimum touch target** from design tokens. This applies to:\n- Tag chip hit areas (even if visually smaller)\n- Card action icons (edit/delete)\n- FAB\n- \"Clear filters\" text button (padding must compensate for small visual size)\n\n---\n\n## 7. Accessibility Requirements\n\n### 7.1 Semantic Structure\n\n```html\n<main>\n  <section aria-label=\"Search and filter bookmarks\">\n    <label for=\"search-input\" class=\"sr-only\">Search bookmarks</label>\n    <input id=\"search-input\" type=\"search\" … />\n    <div role=\"group\" aria-label=\"Filter by tag\">\n      <button aria-pressed=\"true\">All</button>\n      <button aria-pressed=\"false\">ai</button>\n      <!-- … -->\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section aria-label=\"Bookmark list\" aria-live=\"polite\" aria-atomic=\"false\">\n    <!-- Card grid or state component -->\n  </section>\n</main>\n\n<button aria-label=\"Add new bookmark\" class=\"fab\">+</button>\n```\n\n### 7.2 Live Region Strategy\n\n| Region | `aria-live` | `aria-atomic` | Purpose |\n|--------|------------|---------------|---------|\n| Card grid container | `polite` | `false` | Announces count change when filters update |\n| Toast container | `polite` | `true` | Success/error announcements |\n| Delete confirmation face | `assertive` | `true` | Destructive action needs immediate announcement |\n\n### 7.3 Colour Contrast Audit\n\nUsing PRD colour tokens (playful theme takes precedence over design token system):\n\n| Element | Foreground | Background | Ratio Target | Note |\n|---------|-----------|-----------|-------------|------|\n| Body text on card | `#2D3436` | `#FFEAA7` | ≥ 4.5:1 | Verify: ~10.5:1 ✓ |\n| Muted text (URL) on card | `#636E72` | `#FFEAA7` | ≥ 4.5:1 | Verify: ~4.6:1 — borderline, confirm |\n| Active chip text | `#FFFFFF` | `#6C5CE7` | ≥ 4.5:1 | Verify: ~5.1:1 ✓ |\n| FAB icon | `#FFFFFF` | `#6C5CE7` | ≥ 3:1 (large UI) | ✓ |\n| Danger/delete text | `#FF6B6B` | `#FFEAA7` | ≥ 4.5:1 | **Risk: ~3.2:1 — do not use colour alone for error state; add icon** |\n\n> ⚠️ **Accessibility Flag:** `--color-danger` (`#FF6B6B`) on `--color-surface` (`#FFEAA7`) may fail WCAG AA for small text. Recommend pairing danger colour with a warning icon and/or darkening to `#D63031` for text-only contexts.\n\n### 7.4 Focus Management\n\n- **Initial page load:** Focus on SearchBar (or first interactive element if search is empty-state).\n- **After delete confirmation resolves (either outcome):** Return focus to the next card in DOM order, or the EmptyState CTA if the last bookmark was deleted.\n- **After tag chip toggle:** Focus remains on the toggled chip (do not move focus).\n- **FAB:** On activation, navigate to `/add` — focus moves to first form field on that screen.\n\n### 7.5 Keyboard Navigation Map\n\n| Key | Context | Action |\n|-----|---------|--------|\n| `Tab` | Anywhere | Move focus forward through interactive elements |\n| `Shift+Tab` | Anywhere | Move focus backward |\n| `Enter` / `Space` | Card (not action buttons) | Navigate to Edit or Detail |\n| `Enter` / `Space` | Tag chip | Toggle chip on/off |\n| `Enter` / `Space` | FAB | Navigate to `/add` |\n| `Escape` | Delete confirmation open | Cancel, revert card, return focus to delete icon |\n| `Escape` | Search input focused | Clear search value |\n\n---\n\n## 8. Visual Design Direction\n\n### 8.1 Theme Application\n\nThe PRD specifies a **Playful theme** that takes visual precedence over the design token system. Key applications for this screen:\n\n| Token/Element | Value to Apply |\n|---------------|----------------|\n| Page background | `#FFF9E6` (`--color-bg`) |\n| Card background | `#FFEAA7` (`--color-surface`) — warm soft yellow |\n| Primary actions (FAB, active chips, CTA) | `#6C5CE7` (`--color-primary`) |\n| Hover accents | `#00CEC9` (`--color-secondary`) |\n| Headings (EmptyState, NoResults) | `'Fredoka', sans-serif`, 600, 24px |\n| Body / input text | `'Inter', sans-serif`, 400, 15px |\n| Tag chip text | `'Inter', sans-serif`, 500, 12px |\n| Card border-radius | `12px` |\n| Chip / button border-radius | `20px` |\n| Input border-radius | `8px` |\n| Card shadow (rest) | `0 2px 8px rgba(108, 92, 231, 0.10)` |\n| Card shadow (hover) | `0 6px 20px rgba(108, 92, 231, 0.10)` |\n\n### 8.2 Illustration Style (EmptyState)\n\nPer brand spec: **organic line-art with watercolor fills**. For the EmptyState illustration:\n- Subject: A small ribbon bookmark, a few stacked papers/links, maybe a magnifying glass with a small leaf.\n- Fills: Soft washes of sage, terracotta, marigold — no flat vector fills.\n- Accents: A few tiny stars, dots, or leaf doodles scattered around.\n- Animation: Slow opacity pulse (2s infinite alternate, 0.6 → 1.0) on the entire illustration container.\n\n### 8.3 Micro-Interaction Summary\n\n| Trigger | Animation | Duration | Easing |\n|---------|-----------|----------|--------|\n| FAB hover | 360° rotation | 400ms | ease-in-out |\n| Tag chip click | Scale 1.0 → 1.05 → 1.0 | 100ms | spring |\n| Card hover | Shadow lift (rest → hover values) | 200ms | ease |\n| Delete confirmation toggle | Cross-fade (both faces) | 200ms | ease |\n| EmptyState illustration | Opacity 0.6 → 1.0 pulse | 2s infinite alternate | ease-in-out |\n| Toast appearance | Slide down from top + bounce | per cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1) | — |\n| Tag chip active ↔ inactive | Fill/outline style swap | 150ms | ease |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Copy & Tone Guidelines\n\nPer brand spec: *\"Warm and grounded. Speaks like a well-organized friend who enjoys stationery. Gentle affirmations on success, patient explanations on errors. Never rushed.\"*\n\n| Location | Copy | Tone Note |\n|----------|------|-----------|\n| SearchBar placeholder | `\"Search by title or URL…\"` | Specific, inviting |\n| EmptyState heading | `\"No bookmarks yet\"` | Neutral, not negative |\n| EmptyState subtext | `\"Save your first link and it'll live right here.\"` | Warm, forward-looking |\n| EmptyState CTA | `\"Save your first link\"` | Action-oriented, friendly |\n| NoResultsState heading | `\"No bookmarks match your filters\"` | Factual, not apologetic |\n| NoResultsState subtext | `\"Try a different search or clear your filters.\"` | Helpful, patient |\n| NoResultsState CTA | `\"Clear filters\"` | Direct action |\n| Delete confirmation | `\"Delete this bookmark?\"` | Direct, no dramatics |\n| Delete confirm button | `\"Yes, delete it\"` | Conversational |\n| Delete cancel button | `\"Keep it\"` | Friendly alternative to \"Cancel\" |\n| FAB `aria-label` | `\"Add new bookmark\"` | Descriptive for screen readers |\n\n---\n\n## 10. Edge Cases & Risk Flags\n\n### 10.1 Identified Edge Cases\n\n| Scenario | Expected Behaviour | Design Consideration |\n|----------|-------------------|----------------------|\n| User has 50+ bookmarks | Grid scrolls; filter is essential for usability | Consider showing result count (\"Showing 12 of 50\") |\n| User has 20+ unique tags | Tag chip row becomes very long | Horizontal scroll is mandatory; consider a \"show more tags\" collapse on desktop |\n| Tag name is very long (up to 20 chars) | Chip may be wide | Chips should have `max-width` with truncation + tooltip on hover |\n| Bookmark title is exactly 60 chars | Ellipsis at exact cutoff | Test truncation rendering across browsers |\n| Multiple delete confirmations open simultaneously | Should not be possible | Ensure clicking delete on a second card collapses any other open confirmation first |\n| Filter active + user adds new bookmark | New bookmark should appear immediately if it matches current filters | BookmarkStore subscription / reactive state required |\n| No tags exist (all bookmarks untagged) | TagFilterChips row shows only \"All\" | \"All\" chip should still render; row height should not collapse to zero |\n| Bookmark has 5 tags (all visible) | \"+N\" overflow not shown | Only show \"+N\" when N > 0 (i.e. 4th+ tag exists) |\n\n### 10.2 Risk Flags\n\n> ⚠️ **Risk 1 — Colour Contrast:** `--color-danger` (`#FF6B6B`) on `--color-surface` (`#FFEAA7`) fails WCAG AA for small text (~3.2:1). Resolve by using `#D63031` for danger text, or supplement colour with an icon.\n\n> ⚠️ **Risk 2 — Muted Text Contrast:** `--color-muted` (`#636E72`) on `#FFEAA7` is borderline (~4.6:1). Verify in production; if failing, darken muted token to `#4A5568`.\n\n> ⚠️ **Risk 3 — Tag Chip Row on Mobile:** With many tags, horizontal scroll without a visible scroll affordance is a discoverability problem. Recommend a subtle fade-out gradient on the right edge to signal scrollability.\n\n> ⚠️ **Risk 4 — Auto-revert Timer (5s Delete):** If users are reading the confirmation slowly (e.g. low literacy, cognitive load), 5 seconds may feel abrupt. Consider a subtle visual countdown indicator on the confirmation face to set expectation.\n\n> ⚠️ **Risk 5 — FAB Obscuring Content:** On mobile with a full 1-column list, the FAB may cover the delete/edit actions of the last card. Ensure the last card has bottom padding equal to FAB height + safe area inset.\n\n---\n\n## 11. Success Metrics\n\n| Metric | Target | Measurement Method |\n|--------|--------|--------------------|\n| Time-to-first-bookmark-found | < 5 seconds with known tag or title fragment | Usability test task timing |\n| Filter comprehension | ≥ 90% of users understand AND logic without instruction | Think-aloud usability testing |\n| Delete confirmation reversal rate | < 10% of delete initiations are cancelled (indicates UX is clear, not alarming) | Interaction analytics |\n| EmptyState CTA click rate (first session) | ≥ 70% of new users click through to add first bookmark | Funnel analytics |\n| Accessibility audit pass rate | 100% WCAG AA on automated + manual audit | axe-core + manual screen reader test |\n\n---\n\n## 12. Open Questions for Design Review\n\n1. **Tag chip row overflow on desktop:** Should chips wrap to a second row (consuming vertical space) or always scroll horizontally? Wrapping increases discoverability but disrupts layout rhythm.\n2. **Result count display:** Should the screen show \"Showing X bookmarks\" when filters are active? This aids orientation but adds visual noise.\n3. **Card click target:** Should the entire card be clickable (navigating to Detail/Edit), or only the explicit action buttons? Full-card click is more mobile-friendly but creates ambiguity on desktop with hover-revealed actions.\n4. **Sort order:** The PRD does not specify card sort order. Assume reverse-chronological (`createdAt` descending) as the default? Should a sort control be considered?\n5. **Tag chip row accessibility on mobile:** Is horizontal scroll with keyboard navigation achievable without a custom scroll-into-view implementation? Plan needed.\n6. **\"+N\" overflow chips:** Should clicking the \"+N\" pill expand the card to show all tags inline, or navigate to the Detail screen? PRD is silent on this interaction.\n\n---\n\n*This brief should be used as the primary input for wireframing, component specification, and accessibility review. All interaction patterns and copy decisions made during design should be cross-referenced against Section 4 (Component Specifications), Section 7 (Accessibility Requirements), and Section 10 (Edge Cases & Risk Flags).*"
}